      "ticker": "BA",
      "score": 88,
      "action": "BUY",
      "entity": "THE BOEING COMPANY",
      "narrative": "# CORRUPTION BRIEF: THE BOEING COMPANY (BA)\n\n**Date of Signal: May 6, 2026 | Contracts: $32.9B+ NASA Awards**\n\n---\n\nThe Boeing Company received two NASA contract awards totaling approximately **$32.9 billion** — a **$22.4 billion** primary contract and a **$10.5 billion** supplemental award — on May 6, 2026, representing one of the largest dual-contract NASA allocations to a single defense and aerospace contractor in recent federal procurement history. Boeing holds a documented history of NASA contract dependency, including the **Space Launch System (SLS) program**, which has faced repeated congressional scrutiny over cost overruns exceeding **$6 billion above original estimates** per GAO reporting. Federal procurement records show Boeing has received **over $163 billion** in government contracts over the past decade, with NASA and DoD awards consistently following periods of active lobbying expenditure, which totaled **$15.3 million in 2023** per OpenSecrets filings. The pattern of large-scale sole-source and limited-competition NASA awards to Boeing has been flagged in **three separate GAO reports (2019, 2021, 2023)** citing insufficient competitive bidding protocols in major space system procurements.\n\n---\n\n*Sources: USASpending.gov, GAO Reports GAO-19-554, GAO-21-105, GAO-23-106, OpenSecrets.org, NASA OIG procurement audits.*\n\n*No speculation. Facts only.*"
